    <div class="container px-5 my-5">
        <div class="row gx-5 justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-lg-10 col-xl-7">
                <div class="text-center">
                    <div class="h3 mb-4">
                        <em>"Working with Medbase has saved me tons of studying time 
                        when preparing for tests!
                         I am now more efficient in studying because I have a ready source of 
                         questions to quiz myself at the end of the day."</em>
                     </div>
                    <div class="d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center">
                        <div class="fw-bold h6">
                            Tadiwanashe Mawere
                            <span class="fw-bold text-primary mx-1">/</span>
                            Nursing, UZ
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!--How to Sections-->
<div class="py-5" id="howtoSection">
    <div class="container px-5 my-5">
        <div class="row gx-5 align-items-center justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-xl-7">
                <img class="img-fluid rounded-3 my-5"
                     src="~/img/how_to.svg" alt="..." />
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-8 col-xl-5 text-center">
                <div class="text-dark">
                    <h2 class="text-dark">How to use Medbase</h2>

                    <p class="lead fw-normal text-muted mb-0">
                        You can load question with or without answers.
                        We suggest you first attempt the questions without seeing the answers. 
                        You will remember the content better that way.
                    </p>
                    <br/>
                    <p class="lead fw-normal text-muted mb-0">
                        Medicine is a big field, as such some answers may be wrong due to errors in transcription or something else. 
                        <br/>
                        If you find a question with a wrong answer, we have placed a button on each question so that you can give us your suggested answer and that we make the necessary adjustments. 
                        <br/>
                        We, and other students would greatly appreciate your feedback.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<hr/>
